article.headline: Lehigh 31, Lafayette 15
article.story: EASTON, Pa. -- J.B. Clark threw two touchdown passes and John Kennedy had a 94-yard interception return for a touchdown as Lehigh beat rival Lafayette 31-15 on Saturday in the 144th meeting between the two teams. Clark had touchdown passes of 29 yards to Mike Fitzgerald and 14 yards to Nick Johnson for Lehigh (5-6, 4-2 Patriot League) and the swarming Mountain Hawk defense recorded eight sacks and two interceptions. Lehigh built a 17-12 halftime lead on Clark's two touchdown passes and a 40-yard field goal by Jason Leo. Davis Rodriguez kicked a 22-yard field goal in the third for Lafayette (7-4, 3-3) to cut Lehigh's lead to 17-15. Adam Watson scored on a 1-yard run in the fourth to push the Mountain Hawks' lead to 24-15 with 7:11 left in the fourth. Led by backup quarterback Rob Curley, Lafayette drove down to the Lehigh 10-yard line with just under five minutes to go, but Kennedy intercepted a pass by Curley at the 6-yard line and returned it all the way back for a touchdown to seal the victory. Clark was 12-for-22 for 201 yards and Fitzgerald had five catches for 101 yards for Lehigh, which was outgained 321 yards to 214. Curley completed 10 of 19 passes for 122 yards but Quilling was just 5-for-13 for 57 yards for Lafayette. Shaun Adair had a 62-yard touchdown run on a reverse in the first quarter and combined with DeAndre Morrow to rush for 147 yards for the Leopards, who held Lehigh to just 13 yards rushing.
